      "text": "Meyer, CSS expert, writes about on his personal Web site; it&#039;s largely Web standards and Web technology, but also various bits of culture, politics, personal observations, and other miscellaneous stuff</description> <lastBuildDate>Fri, 19 Dec 2025 15:45:01 +0000</lastBuildDate> <language>en-US</language> <sy:updatePeriod> hourly </sy:updatePeriod> <sy:updateFrequency> 1 </sy:updateFrequency> <item> <title>Targeting by Reference in the Shadow DOM</title> <link>https://meyerweb.com/eric/thoughts/2025/12/19/targeting-by-reference-in-the-shadow-dom/</link> <comments>https://meyerweb.com/eric/thoughts/2025/12/19/targeting-by-reference-in-the-shadow-dom/#comments</comments> <dc:creator><![CDATA[Eric Meyer]]></dc:creator> <pubDate>Fri, 19 Dec 2025 15:04:58 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[DOM]]></category> <category><![CDATA[JavaScript]]></category> <category><![CDATA[Standards]]></category> <guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://meyerweb.com/eric/thoughts/?p=5723</guid> <description><![CDATA[A new way to allow elements inside a Shadow DOM to be targeted for accessibility or other reasons.]]></description> <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I’ve long made it clear that I don’t particularly care for the whole Shadow <abbr title=\"Document Object Model\">DOM</abbr> thing.",
